    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-12T19:11:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-12T19:11:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–1251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d479fn1">Repeated for information to Pretoria as
                        125.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-12T19:11:00-05:00"
                            >December 12, 1951—7:11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 428. We have been advised that <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> Malan intends issue this eve statement
                    announcing temporary withdrawal South African Del from <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> and recall of Donges for consultation. If statement is actually
                    issued <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> will not issue press statement but
                    in response questions will say “We regret that the South African Govt has
                    decided to withdraw its Del from the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. We note that the withdrawal is temporary and
                    hope that on further consideration the South African Govt will decide to return
                    its Del to the <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>.”</p>
                <p>Suggest Del and <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> fol same line.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
